Project Abstract
This project is a sentiment analysis and aggregation web application. Users can search for any set of keywords (e.g. a
brand name or topic) and they will see both a graphical and tabular presentation of public opinion regarding their
search. The result data presented to the user will be constructed from social media posts that are processed through
a natural language processing engine. Users will see public sentiment changes over time and can break down results
by social media platform and demographics. This application is targeted toward consumers, who can research
sentiment regarding potential purchases; brand managers, who can assess the effectiveness of their marketing
campaigns across demographic groups; and investors, who can interpret public sentiment to predict market
fluctuation.
Project Description
Nowadays, there is more data than ever. Social media has produced a large amount of textual data that can be
simplified using sentiment analysis. Through this project, we hope to answer users' questions regarding key trends in
different industries through an in depth analysis of social media usage. This will be a full-stack web application with
an interactive user-interface as well as Sentiment Analysis logic powering it from the back-end. There is also an
established connection with multiple social media sites through a custom API. The interface comes with a dashboard
that will show where top trends lie and growth can be improved as well.
